        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 11:43AM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 1143 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Morris to near Mazon to near Odell.
Movement was east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Coal City, Diamond, Mazon, Braceville, South Wilmington, Kinsman,
Reddick, Godley, East Brooklyn, Gardner, Dwight, Verona, Carbon Hill,
Morris, and Braidwood.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building. Frequent
cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
